Last night, Rodriguez rejected the compromise amendment, turning his back on digital creators and a Senate process lauded as one of the most comprehensive ever. Title: The AsyncIterator interface - Without boats, dreams dry up
Description:
In a previous post, I established the notion of ‚Äúregisters‚Äù - code in Rust can be
written in different registers, and it‚Äôs important to adequately support all registers. I
specifically discussed the low-level interface of the AsyncIterator trait, about which there is
currently a debate. The interface it currently has is a method called poll_next, which is a ‚Äúpoll‚Äù
method like Future::poll. Poll methods are very ‚Äúlow-level‚Äù and are harder to write correctly than
async functions. Some people would like to see AsyncIterator shifted to have an async next method,
simply the ‚Äúasyncified‚Äù Iterator trait.
